ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: In a typical week, how many hours do you spend attending individual supervision?
In a typical week, how many hours do you spend attending group supervision?
We discussed and spent time reviewing paperwork, signing charts and notes, discussing billing and scheduling, and other administrative tasks.
We discussed suicide risk, mandated reporting, placement disruption, or other crisis issues.
We discussed issues related to case management such as communicating with other providers, agencies, or external resources or collateral supports.
We discussed issues related to client attendance and spent time problem-solving attendance or engagement issues.
We discussed how to best set agendas with my clients to improve structure and pacing of therapy sessions.
We discussed how to review my client's homework from prior session to best develop the skills discussed with my client in session.
We discussed how to identify the cognitive behavioral interventions that would be the best match for supporting my clients in achieving their therapy goals.
We discussed or practiced how to apply specific cognitive behavioral interventions in sessions with my clients to support them in achieving their therapy goals.
We discussed how to plan my client's out-of-session practice to foster opportunities for skill practice to support my client's overall improvement.
We discussed how to administer, score, or interpret ongoing data (e.g., standardized rating scales) collected from my clients to inform treatment planning.
How confident are you that the answers you provided in this measure accurately reflect what you did in your supervision session?
Notes: 1=Not At All Confident; 4 = Somewhat Confident; 7=Very Confident

ElementDescription: How would you rate the overall quality of the supervision you received in this meeting? Please rate the overall quality of YOUR SUPERVISOR'S behavior in this supervision session.
